% \begin{align}
f'(x) &= 0 \text{ when } x = 2 \\ f''(x) &= \ddx f'(x) = \ddx \left[\dfx \right] \\ &= \underbrace{\dfrac{(x-1)\ddx (x-2) - (x-2)\ddx (x-1)}{\left(x-1 \right)^2}}_{\text{Quotient Rule}} \\ &= \ddfx > 0 \text{ for all }x \neq 1 \end{align} %text Hence, we have an extrema at $x=2$. And $f''(2) > 0 \implies $minima at $x=2$%
